In this statement, President Barack Obama reflects on the 30th anniversary of the seizure of the American Embassy in Tehran. He acknowledges the impact it had on the lives of the American hostages and expresses gratitude for their service and sacrifice. Obama emphasizes the desire of the United States to move beyond the past and establish a relationship with Iran based on mutual interests and respect. He highlights that the US does not interfere in Iran's internal affairs, condemns terrorist attacks against Iran, and recognizes Iran's right to peaceful nuclear power. Obama also mentions the willingness of the US to take confidence-building steps and assist Iran in meeting its medical needs. He states that if Iran fulfills its obligations, it can have a more prosperous relationship with the international community. The president urges Iran to consider what kind of future it wants and whether it will focus on the past or make choices that lead to greater opportunities, prosperity, and justice for its people.